    public class Digit
extends StaticActor

    Digit

    The Digit class is used to create the single bit of scoreBoard and change the image when Score changed.

    A Digit object is set in Map. It represents the current Score of game and change the points when Score added or subtracted.

    Note: This class extends StaticActor abstract class.

    1.0

    • Constructor Detail

      • Digit

        public Digit​(int n,
             int size,
             double x,
             double y)

        The constructor of Digit class to generate instance

        This constructor sets the Digit in the given position x and y in the Map. And set the initial image with the given size and number n.

        Parameters:
        n - The image index (If n == 0, then the image will be "0.png")
        size - The size of the image
        x - The position of x in the Map where digit stays
        y - The position of y in the Map where digit stays
